    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The town’s historic lighthouse, built in 1887, still stands on South Peninsula Drive and offers panoramic ocean views.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.florida-backroads-travel.com/ponce-inlet-florida.html"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "A small museum on Beach Street preserves local history in a restored Florida Cracker duplex, operated by the town.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1,
        4
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.florida-backroads-travel.com/ponce-inlet-florida.html"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Ponce Inlet sits on a barrier island peninsula between the Halifax River and Atlantic Ocean, giving it unique coastal geography.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        12
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ponce_Inlet%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "The town enforces strict land‑use regulations to protect its shoreline and maintain its historic character.",
